1
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:34,694
Everyone knows alcohol is bad for you.

2
00:01:35,361 --> 00:01:36,563
But it does make people happy.

3
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:40,800
True.

4
00:01:41,468 --> 00:01:42,936
Even being cautious can't protect you from every storm.

5
00:01:43,069 --> 00:01:43,970
A little drink won't hurt.

6
00:01:46,306 --> 00:01:47,874
If anything comes up after you get back, tell me.

7
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:49,042
I'll help arrange time off.

8
00:01:49,676 --> 00:01:50,643
Get yourself back in shape.

9
00:01:51,411 --> 00:01:52,745
Life still has to go on.

10
00:01:55,248 --> 00:01:55,715
Here's to you.

11
00:02:09,195 --> 00:02:09,762
Let me tell you something

12
00:02:09,762 --> 00:02:10,964
from the bottom of my heart.

13
00:02:12,599 --> 00:02:13,533
I was parachuted in,

14
00:02:14,434 --> 00:02:16,002
alone at Dongli,

15
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:17,770
without a single trusted aide.

16
00:02:18,671 --> 00:02:19,372
But fortunately,

17
00:02:20,039 --> 00:02:21,574
I have someone as capable

18
00:02:21,641 --> 00:02:22,408
as you in the department.

19
00:02:23,042 --> 00:02:23,610
Anyway,

20
00:02:24,043 --> 00:02:24,511
thank you.

21
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:27,714
I'm the one who should thank you

22
00:02:28,248 --> 00:02:28,948
for helping me so much.

23
00:02:30,483 --> 00:02:31,084
Everyone, everyone.

24
00:02:31,651 --> 00:02:32,152
Come on.

25
00:02:32,585 --> 00:02:34,053
Raise your glasses.

26
00:02:34,120 --> 00:02:34,954
Let me say a few words.

27
00:02:35,121 --> 00:02:35,522
All right.

28
00:02:35,922 --> 00:02:37,590
Director Lin, is that really wine?

29
00:02:37,891 --> 00:02:38,625
Let me top you up.

30
00:02:38,825 --> 00:02:39,325
Thank you.

31
00:02:41,494 --> 00:02:43,329
Meeting abroad like this

32
00:02:43,396 --> 00:02:44,130
must be fate.

33
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:45,231
This one's to everyone.

34
00:02:45,632 --> 00:02:46,766
Eat and drink your fill.

35
00:02:46,866 --> 00:02:47,333
Cheers.

36
00:02:48,935 --> 00:02:49,602
Director Lin.

37
00:02:49,636 --> 00:02:50,303
Come on.

38
00:02:52,605 --> 00:02:53,006
Director.

39
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:54,040
Xiao Lin.

40
00:02:54,807 --> 00:02:55,241
Director.

41
00:03:17,764 --> 00:03:18,464
Dr. Fang.

42
00:03:18,665 --> 00:03:19,265
The reference data you asked for

43
00:03:19,265 --> 00:03:20,466
benchmark data on nurse-to-bed ratios

44
00:03:20,466 --> 00:03:21,601
I've spent the past two days compiling it.

45
00:03:21,601 --> 00:03:22,368
I'll send it to you.

46
00:03:24,771 --> 00:03:25,838
Great. Thank you, Xiao Yang.

47
00:03:50,096 --> 00:03:50,763
Boss Xiaorui,

48
00:03:50,997 --> 00:03:52,465
you said the custom order would be ready in a month.

49
00:03:52,832 --> 00:03:53,967
Isn't it time to ship?

50
00:04:04,644 --> 00:04:05,645
A lot of customers

51
00:04:05,645 --> 00:04:07,347
still don't know what happened to Xiaorui.

52
00:04:07,347 --> 00:04:08,247
Should I post something?

53
00:04:17,824 --> 00:04:18,925
I'll send it out tomorrow.

54
00:04:19,125 --> 00:04:19,826
Sorry for the wait.

55
00:05:04,437 --> 00:05:05,371
Easy, easy.

56
00:05:05,371 --> 00:05:05,838
I'm fine.

57
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:06,439
I'm fine.

58
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:07,674
The show starts soon.

59
00:05:07,707 --> 00:05:09,175
The show. I already bought tickets.

60
00:05:10,843 --> 00:05:11,444
All right.

61
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:12,312
Old Qin, you're too kind.

62
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:13,413
All right.

63
00:05:14,213 --> 00:05:14,647
Director Lin.

64
00:05:15,114 --> 00:05:16,282
You're really not coming with us?

65
00:05:16,549 --> 00:05:17,850
I already bought the tickets.

66
00:05:18,251 --> 00:05:18,985
I'll pass.

67
00:05:19,986 --> 00:05:21,487
Then I'll call you a car.

68
00:05:21,554 --> 00:05:22,255
No, no.

69
00:05:22,288 --> 00:05:23,823
I'm not drunk. I'm perfectly clearheaded.

70
00:05:24,824 --> 00:05:25,625
Turn off the alarm.

71
00:05:26,125 --> 00:05:26,893
Get a good night's sleep.

72
00:05:27,727 --> 00:05:28,227
Thank you, Director.

73
00:05:29,696 --> 00:05:30,063
Let's go.

74
00:05:30,196 --> 00:05:31,130
After you, Director Sheng.

75
00:05:31,631 --> 00:05:32,465
We're off, then.

76
00:05:32,565 --> 00:05:33,266
See you.

77
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:35,034
This way.

78
00:05:35,368 --> 00:05:37,003
Let's go.

79
00:05:37,370 --> 00:05:37,837
Director Lin.

80
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:39,405
Shall we head back to the hotel together?

81
00:05:40,606 --> 00:05:41,274
You go ahead.

82
00:05:41,674 --> 00:05:42,842
I want to walk around by myself.

83
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:44,444
All right.

84
00:05:44,844 --> 00:05:45,678
Be careful.

85
00:05:45,912 --> 00:05:47,280
Call anytime if you need anything.

86
00:07:32,718 --> 00:07:33,519
Death,

87
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:35,588
though the end of life,

88
00:07:36,622 --> 00:07:38,558
is also the end of all suffering.

89
00:08:00,012 --> 00:08:00,847
When a person dies,

90
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:02,315
thyroxine

91
00:08:02,548 --> 00:08:04,183
and adrenaline stop being released.

92
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:05,985
Breathing and heartbeat cease.

93
00:08:06,919 --> 00:08:08,187
Brain waves disappear.

94
00:08:09,722 --> 00:08:10,423
Game over.

95
00:08:11,123 --> 00:08:11,824
That's all.

96
00:08:12,592 --> 00:08:13,759
The moment we're born,

97
00:08:14,227 --> 00:08:15,361
our death is already certain.

98
00:08:15,761 --> 00:08:16,762
For some, it's at eighty.

99
00:08:17,129 --> 00:08:17,964
For some, sixty.

100
00:08:17,964 --> 00:08:18,865
For some, forty.

101
00:08:19,599 --> 00:08:20,833
For some, maybe tomorrow.

102
00:08:22,235 --> 00:08:24,437
Did he really have to be so noble?

103
00:08:26,372 --> 00:08:28,808
He saved so many people.

104
00:08:30,309 --> 00:08:32,712
Why couldn't he have saved my life instead?

105
00:08:36,315 --> 00:08:36,782
Yi.

106
00:08:37,783 --> 00:08:38,851
I believe my dad

107
00:08:39,385 --> 00:08:40,786
would understand your choice too.

108
00:08:42,388 --> 00:08:43,489
Because you're doctors,

109
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:45,725
I've already been incredibly fortunate.

110
00:08:46,926 --> 00:08:48,694
Being able to become family with all of you—

111
00:08:49,195 --> 00:08:50,563
I feel my life

112
00:08:51,130 --> 00:08:51,831
was complete.

113
00:08:52,331 --> 00:08:53,065
You brat.

114
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:54,834
You have to live to a hundred.

115
00:08:55,067 --> 00:08:55,801
Lin Yi.

116
00:08:56,636 --> 00:08:57,803
Let's get married.

117
00:09:02,675 --> 00:09:03,910
Let me be your family.

118
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:54,226
How are things over there today?

119
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,728
Are you back at the hotel?

120
00:10:12,945 --> 00:10:13,412
Brother.

121
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:14,480
You're up early.

122
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:16,248
I brought breakfast.

123
00:10:16,615 --> 00:10:17,516
Eat, then we'll go to work together.

124
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:19,852
Come in.

125
00:10:40,639 --> 00:10:42,074
Most of the moving prep is done.

126
00:10:47,279 --> 00:10:48,080
Have you found a place?

127
00:10:48,547 --> 00:10:49,949
I've contacted an agent.

128
00:10:50,282 --> 00:10:51,917
They're looking for something suitable.

129
00:10:54,587 --> 00:10:55,588
You barely slept last night, did you?

130
00:10:57,990 --> 00:10:58,824
How many hours?

131
00:11:00,593 --> 00:11:01,927
Actual sleep time?

132
00:11:03,229 --> 00:11:03,929
Two hours.

133
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:07,333
What about you?

134
00:11:09,135 --> 00:11:10,036
I came straight from the hospital.

135
00:11:15,041 --> 00:11:15,775
Then later,

136
00:11:15,808 --> 00:11:16,742
we can go back together.

137
00:11:21,814 --> 00:11:22,815
I haven't had this in ages.

138
00:11:25,484 --> 00:11:26,485
Still smells amazing.

139
00:11:37,229 --> 00:11:39,265
Continue straight for two kilometers.

140
00:12:12,998 --> 00:12:13,399
Director.

141
00:12:14,333 --> 00:12:15,134
Why are you here?

142
00:12:15,367 --> 00:12:16,469
Aren't you supposed to return tomorrow?

143
00:12:17,169 --> 00:12:18,170
The first thing I did after landing

144
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:19,438
was come report to you.

145
00:12:19,605 --> 00:12:20,773
How was everything?

146
00:12:21,173 --> 00:12:21,907
Very smooth.

147
00:12:22,108 --> 00:12:23,809
The only torture was

148
00:12:23,876 --> 00:12:25,077
sitting on the plane for over ten hours.

149
00:12:26,545 --> 00:12:27,513
I brought you

150
00:12:27,546 --> 00:12:29,115
some coffee beans from Spain.

151
00:12:29,448 --> 00:12:29,949
Take a look.

152
00:12:31,717 --> 00:12:32,551
They smell good.

153
00:12:32,752 --> 00:12:33,252
Thanks.

154
00:12:33,919 --> 00:12:34,854
What else?

155
00:12:34,920 --> 00:12:35,721
Did the conference go smoothly?

156
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:36,555
Very smoothly.

157
00:12:36,789 --> 00:12:37,690
During the day, we sat in meetings,

158
00:12:37,923 --> 00:12:39,191
feeling like

159
00:12:39,391 --> 00:12:40,626
we were taking endless

160
00:12:40,693 --> 00:12:41,794
listening exams.

161
00:12:42,161 --> 00:12:42,928
But evenings were fine.

162
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:44,330
Some colleagues from China

163
00:12:44,363 --> 00:12:45,598
would get together and chat.

164
00:12:47,199 --> 00:12:47,767
What about Lin Yi?

165
00:12:48,167 --> 00:12:48,734
How was he?

166
00:12:50,136 --> 00:12:51,170
At first,

167
00:12:51,504 --> 00:12:53,072
he didn't seem well.

168
00:12:53,305 --> 00:12:55,174
But after a few days, he seemed better.

169
00:12:56,408 --> 00:12:57,376
Only at dinner,

170
00:12:57,409 --> 00:12:58,410
he kept drinking.

171
00:12:58,677 --> 00:12:59,311
He drank?

172
00:13:01,647 --> 00:13:02,448
A lot?

173
00:13:02,948 --> 00:13:03,783
Not really.

174
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:05,551
I never saw him drunk.

175
00:13:08,087 --> 00:13:09,855
I originally offered to drink for him,

176
00:13:10,022 --> 00:13:11,724
but Director Sheng said a little

177
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:12,424
was fine.

178
00:13:13,025 --> 00:13:14,894
He said Director Lin might sleep better

179
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:15,928
after having some.

180
00:13:16,162 --> 00:13:17,096
So I...

181
00:13:18,664 --> 00:13:19,231
I understand.

182
00:13:19,732 --> 00:13:20,833
All right, Director.

183
00:13:21,167 --> 00:13:21,834
I'll let you work.

184
00:13:22,268 --> 00:13:23,435
I'll go say hello to everyone,

185
00:13:23,669 --> 00:13:24,436
then head home.

186
00:13:24,603 --> 00:13:25,037
Okay.

187
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:45,591
Hello, Xiao Qu.

188
00:13:47,092 --> 00:13:47,793
Yes, go ahead.

189
00:13:49,295 --> 00:13:50,529
Wednesday?

190
00:13:51,931 --> 00:13:53,666
Wednesday evening works.

191
00:13:56,068 --> 00:13:57,169
Can we also see

192
00:13:57,169 --> 00:13:58,237
the unit on the seventh floor?

193
00:13:58,637 --> 00:14:00,206
Or anything with similar conditions.

194
00:14:00,239 --> 00:14:01,774
I'd like to view several at once.

195
00:14:03,209 --> 00:14:03,642
All right.

196
00:14:03,842 --> 00:14:04,743
I'll wait for your update.

197
00:14:05,945 --> 00:14:06,478
Bye.

198
00:14:13,352 --> 00:14:14,119
Goodbye, Dr. Fang.

199
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:14,753
Bye.

200
00:14:20,192 --> 00:14:21,527
Why are you here?

201
00:14:26,565 --> 00:14:27,466
To pick you up from work.

202
00:14:28,601 --> 00:14:29,969
Didn't we agree to meet at home?

203
00:14:31,170 --> 00:14:32,071
There was nothing for me to do

204
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:32,771
sitting there alone.

205
00:14:33,205 --> 00:14:34,406
I couldn't wait to see you.

206
00:14:45,985 --> 00:14:46,919
Put that down.

207
00:14:49,255 --> 00:14:50,956
Why didn't you tell me beforehand?

208
00:14:51,357 --> 00:14:52,625
What if we missed each other?

209
00:14:53,025 --> 00:14:53,525
Impossible.

210
00:14:54,493 --> 00:14:55,361
We won't miss each other.

211
00:15:12,044 --> 00:15:13,712
How was the trip?

212
00:15:16,148 --> 00:15:18,083
A little boring.

213
00:15:18,117 --> 00:15:19,051
Not much useful content.

214
00:15:19,785 --> 00:15:20,986
But getting away

215
00:15:21,453 --> 00:15:22,187
was still nice.

216
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:24,023
It really is beautiful there.

217
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:26,892
Yeah.

218
00:15:27,026 --> 00:15:27,493
Here.

219
00:15:28,093 --> 00:15:28,627
This is for you.

220
00:15:29,295 --> 00:15:29,762
What's this?

221
00:15:30,396 --> 00:15:30,996
A gift.

222
00:15:32,231 --> 00:15:33,866
Since when did you learn

223
00:15:33,932 --> 00:15:35,534
to bring back gifts from business trips?

224
00:15:37,636 --> 00:15:38,404
This is very famous.

225
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:39,638
Director Sheng said it was delicious.

226
00:15:49,682 --> 00:15:50,549
It is pretty good.

227
00:15:52,318 --> 00:15:53,385
His recommendation was right.

228
00:15:57,523 --> 00:15:58,557
When I got home today,

229
00:15:58,791 --> 00:15:59,725
I saw you'd packed away

230
00:15:59,758 --> 00:16:00,559
all of Xiaorui's things.

231
00:16:03,562 --> 00:16:04,096
Yeah.

232
00:16:04,763 --> 00:16:06,231
We have so much stuff,

233
00:16:06,732 --> 00:16:07,866
so I thought we'd pack little by little.

234
00:16:11,570 --> 00:16:12,071
By the way,

235
00:16:12,404 --> 00:16:13,672
the agent called today.

236
00:16:13,772 --> 00:16:14,606
There are several places

237
00:16:14,606 --> 00:16:15,908
we can view Wednesday evening.

238
00:16:16,208 --> 00:16:17,042
Let's go together.

239
00:16:22,348 --> 00:16:23,382
Maybe we shouldn't.

240
00:16:26,852 --> 00:16:29,088
Moving is such a hassle.

241
00:16:30,155 --> 00:16:31,123
And we're used to

242
00:16:31,123 --> 00:16:32,157
the place we have now.

243
00:16:32,791 --> 00:16:33,525
It's close to the hospital too.

244
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:34,626
Convenient for work.

245
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:39,264
Are you sure?

246
00:16:42,634 --> 00:16:43,135
I'm sure.

247
00:16:45,104 --> 00:16:46,038
I've thought it through.

248
00:16:46,972 --> 00:16:47,806
Since it happened,

249
00:16:49,441 --> 00:16:50,109
I should face it.

250
00:16:52,611 --> 00:16:53,512
Xiaorui is gone.

251
00:16:56,482 --> 00:16:57,649
I shouldn't keep running away.

252
00:16:58,917 --> 00:16:59,585
If I miss him,

253
00:17:00,352 --> 00:17:01,553
I'll miss him openly.

254
00:17:04,256 --> 00:17:05,157
That house

255
00:17:06,725 --> 00:17:07,826
was once our home.

256
00:17:10,262 --> 00:17:10,996
I hope it can still

257
00:17:11,029 --> 00:17:11,997
be our home in the future.

258
00:17:14,933 --> 00:17:15,567
What do you think?

259
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:21,306
Okay.

260
00:17:29,515 --> 00:17:30,682
You've had a hard few days.

261
00:17:34,119 --> 00:17:35,354
Movie night tonight.

262
00:17:47,633 --> 00:17:48,634
So this old lady

263
00:17:48,634 --> 00:17:50,202
was Rose from the beginning?

264
00:17:51,170 --> 00:17:52,438
You only just realized?

265
00:17:53,238 --> 00:17:55,307
We never finished it before.

266
00:17:57,176 --> 00:17:57,910
It's pretty good.

267
00:17:59,011 --> 00:18:00,145
What should we watch next?

268
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:02,681
You're not sleepy tonight?

269
00:18:03,082 --> 00:18:03,749
No.

270
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:05,084
I'm still jet-lagged.

271
00:18:06,385 --> 00:18:07,653
It's okay. Sleep first if you're tired.

272
00:18:08,487 --> 00:18:09,455
Then I want to keep watching too.

273
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:30,709
Such a brave boy.

274
00:18:30,843 --> 00:18:31,743
Let me take that off for you.

275
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:34,746
Okay. Sit up.

276
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:39,485
Were you scared?

277
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:45,390
Thank you, Uncle Zhou.

278
00:18:46,525 --> 00:18:47,426
Senlin was great.

279
00:18:47,559 --> 00:18:48,894
So brave. Not scared at all.

280
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:51,130
What's there to fear about an exam?

281
00:18:54,066 --> 00:18:54,766
Mom.

282
00:18:55,434 --> 00:18:56,602
I need to poop.

283
00:18:57,035 --> 00:18:57,636
Okay.

284
00:18:58,604 --> 00:18:59,805
Where's the restroom?

285
00:19:00,472 --> 00:19:01,173
I'll take him.

286
00:19:02,007 --> 00:19:02,441
Come on.

287
00:19:03,842 --> 00:19:04,343
Thank you.

288
00:19:13,085 --> 00:19:13,919
Thank you.

289
00:19:16,455 --> 00:19:17,689
I didn't get a chance to ask earlier.

290
00:19:17,923 --> 00:19:18,891
How were the results?

291
00:19:19,791 --> 00:19:21,226
No obvious progression.

292
00:19:21,493 --> 00:19:22,227
Still early-stage.

293
00:19:22,427 --> 00:19:23,395
You've protected him well.

294
00:19:25,330 --> 00:19:25,998
But

295
00:19:26,231 --> 00:19:27,866
his cardiac workload

296
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:29,234
will most likely keep increasing.

297
00:19:30,002 --> 00:19:31,370
He still needs to avoid strenuous exercise.

298
00:19:31,436 --> 00:19:32,104
And he can't catch colds.

299
00:19:32,271 --> 00:19:32,905
If he feels any discomfort,

300
00:19:32,905 --> 00:19:33,839
pay attention immediately.

301
00:19:35,307 --> 00:19:36,108
I understand.

302
00:19:37,609 --> 00:19:39,144
A single infection

303
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:40,245
or other trigger

304
00:19:40,279 --> 00:19:41,813
could cause his condition to deteriorate rapidly.

305
00:19:42,281 --> 00:19:44,016
So I'm always on guard.

306
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:45,651
It's just that

307
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:46,852
every time he has a checkup,

308
00:19:46,985 --> 00:19:48,554
I still feel anxious.

309
00:19:48,987 --> 00:19:49,855
I'm terrified of seeing

310
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,323
any red arrows on the report.

311
00:19:52,991 --> 00:19:53,825
Sometimes,

312
00:19:53,926 --> 00:19:55,427
when I see him lying beside me,

313
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:56,628
I wonder

314
00:19:57,529 --> 00:19:58,363
whether I'll get to

315
00:19:58,363 --> 00:19:59,431
watch him grow up,

316
00:20:00,332 --> 00:20:01,733
go to college,

317
00:20:02,067 --> 00:20:03,001
and have a girlfriend.

318
00:20:05,571 --> 00:20:06,672
But no matter what,

319
00:20:07,439 --> 00:20:08,507
I'll do everything I can.

320
00:20:09,408 --> 00:20:10,108
Mom.

321
00:20:12,110 --> 00:20:12,878
Did you wash your hands?

322
00:20:13,245 --> 00:20:14,046
All done.

323
00:20:14,746 --> 00:20:15,547
Such a good boy.

324
00:20:16,214 --> 00:20:17,583
Senlin did so well today.

325
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:18,951
Uncle will reward you with a cake.

326
00:20:18,951 --> 00:20:19,518
How about it?

327
00:20:22,087 --> 00:20:22,554
Is that okay?

328
00:20:24,156 --> 00:20:24,756
Want some?

329
00:20:26,525 --> 00:20:27,092
Sure.

330
00:20:29,328 --> 00:20:29,761
Let's go.

331
00:20:40,038 --> 00:20:40,973
Can you hear it?

332
00:20:42,107 --> 00:20:43,408
No.

333
00:20:47,613 --> 00:20:48,280
Now I can.

334
00:20:48,614 --> 00:20:49,915
The doctor's heartbeat

335
00:20:50,015 --> 00:20:50,849
is a little fast.

336
00:21:01,827 --> 00:21:03,795
I didn't say anything just now.

337
00:21:04,429 --> 00:21:05,764
You should at least say something.

338
00:21:07,532 --> 00:21:09,334
Are you singing?

339
00:21:31,757 --> 00:21:32,357
Lin Yi.

340
00:21:35,694 --> 00:21:36,495
Where are you going?

341
00:21:36,995 --> 00:21:37,496
I...

342
00:21:39,031 --> 00:21:39,931
I'm getting ready for surgery.

343
00:21:40,432 --> 00:21:41,333
It's your first day back.

344
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:42,000
You're already operating?

345
00:21:42,267 --> 00:21:43,135
Why not rest a few more days?

346
00:21:43,535 --> 00:21:44,803
I've rested too long.

347
00:21:44,836 --> 00:21:46,238
The surgeries are piling up.

348
00:21:47,906 --> 00:21:48,607
What time will you finish?

349
00:21:49,174 --> 00:21:49,908
Don't forget

350
00:21:49,908 --> 00:21:50,609
you have a psychology appointment today.

351
00:21:51,877 --> 00:21:53,645
Maybe I won't go.

352
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:55,047
I'm better. I'm fine.

353
00:21:57,049 --> 00:21:57,549
All right, then.

354
00:21:58,050 --> 00:21:58,650
Dinner tonight.

355
00:21:59,551 --> 00:22:00,285
I have to go

356
00:22:00,318 --> 00:22:00,919
to Fushan Hospital in a bit.

357
00:22:01,053 --> 00:22:01,253
There's a

358
00:22:01,253 --> 00:22:01,987
TAVR training session.

359
00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:02,954
I don't know when it'll end.

360
00:22:10,429 --> 00:22:11,196
Hello, Director An.

361
00:22:11,863 --> 00:22:12,397
Yes, yes.

362
00:22:12,964 --> 00:22:13,632
I'll definitely be there this afternoon.

363
00:22:14,199 --> 00:22:14,633
Okay.

364
00:22:17,836 --> 00:22:18,470
I'm heading out.

365
00:22:27,346 --> 00:22:27,946
Partner.

366
00:22:33,485 --> 00:22:33,985
Don't worry.

367
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:34,920
I'm fine now.

368
00:22:52,471 --> 00:22:53,038
Director Wu.

369
00:22:55,774 --> 00:22:56,208
Has his

370
00:22:56,208 --> 00:22:56,608
TAVR procedure still not finished?

371
00:22:56,608 --> 00:22:57,275
Not yet.

372
00:22:58,276 --> 00:22:59,611
This is his second case.

373
00:23:00,345 --> 00:23:01,713
What do you mean, his second?

374
00:23:03,482 --> 00:23:04,483
I've been waiting forever.

375
00:23:04,483 --> 00:23:05,450
Wasn't I supposed to go next

376
00:23:05,450 --> 00:23:06,485
after his first case?

377
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:08,487
Because

378
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:10,055
Director Lin's first procedure

379
00:23:10,188 --> 00:23:11,590
finished earlier than expected,

380
00:23:11,923 --> 00:23:12,624
so they brought

381
00:23:12,624 --> 00:23:13,425
the next patient

382
00:23:13,525 --> 00:23:14,359
straight in.

383
00:23:15,293 --> 00:23:15,727
And

384
00:23:15,961 --> 00:23:17,195
Director Sheng called personally,

385
00:23:17,195 --> 00:23:17,996
asking the operating room

386
00:23:17,996 --> 00:23:18,864
to accommodate him.

387
00:23:19,164 --> 00:23:20,265
He said he has a lot of patients.

388
00:23:20,565 --> 00:23:22,067
Please bear with it.

389
00:23:23,135 --> 00:23:24,035
This is ridiculous.

390
00:23:24,236 --> 00:23:25,570
No, Director Wu.

391
00:23:27,005 --> 00:23:28,240
There are five workdays a week,

392
00:23:28,473 --> 00:23:29,408
and Director Lin's

393
00:23:29,408 --> 00:23:29,875
TAVR procedures alone

394
00:23:29,875 --> 00:23:30,709
take up two and a half days.

395
00:23:31,009 --> 00:23:32,043
They also often run

396
00:23:32,043 --> 00:23:32,677
past one in the afternoon.

397
00:23:32,811 --> 00:23:33,678
Our interventional cases

398
00:23:33,745 --> 00:23:34,746
keep getting delayed.

399
00:23:35,046 --> 00:23:35,847
Patients and families

400
00:23:35,881 --> 00:23:36,915
are already complaining.

401
00:23:39,284 --> 00:23:40,118
And today,

402
00:23:40,118 --> 00:23:40,685
who knows how late it'll go?

403
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:42,587
Lately, I often work until midnight.

404
00:23:43,088 --> 00:23:43,789
Exactly, Director.

405
00:23:44,156 --> 00:23:44,489
Besides,

406
00:23:44,489 --> 00:23:44,923
TAVR

407
00:23:44,923 --> 00:23:45,924
was originally our procedure.

408
00:23:46,024 --> 00:23:46,792
Now the patients from

409
00:23:46,792 --> 00:23:47,492
Liu Dong's and my joint clinic

410
00:23:48,226 --> 00:23:49,327
are all being admitted to Cardiac Surgery.

411
00:23:49,494 --> 00:23:50,162
Then all the valve procedures

412
00:23:50,195 --> 00:23:51,430
are done by Director Lin.

413
00:23:51,730 --> 00:23:53,198
What kind of joint clinic is that?

414
00:23:54,366 --> 00:23:55,267
And I heard

415
00:23:56,802 --> 00:23:58,236
they're about to open

416
00:23:58,236 --> 00:23:59,037
a valve clinic.

417
00:23:59,805 --> 00:24:01,273
President Wang has already approved it.

418
00:24:07,879 --> 00:24:08,880
I'll go check

419
00:24:08,914 --> 00:24:10,081
the operating room situation again.

420
00:24:14,152 --> 00:24:14,686
Director.

421
00:24:16,855 --> 00:24:17,722
I'll come too.

422
00:24:57,128 --> 00:24:57,829
Director Lin.

423
00:24:59,130 --> 00:24:59,931
The surgery is over, Director.

424
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:01,132
What is it?

425
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:03,201
I wanted to ask:

426
00:25:03,568 --> 00:25:04,202
the one-stop valve clinic

427
00:25:04,269 --> 00:25:05,637
you mentioned before—

428
00:25:05,704 --> 00:25:06,271
are we still doing it?

429
00:25:06,838 --> 00:25:07,506
Everything is already prepared.

430
00:25:08,206 --> 00:25:08,907
Then when do we start?

431
00:25:11,443 --> 00:25:12,143
Let's hold off for now.

432
00:25:12,711 --> 00:25:13,211
There's no rush.

433
00:25:13,311 --> 00:25:13,912
No need to wait.

434
00:25:14,246 --> 00:25:15,080
We can start now.

435
00:25:20,151 --> 00:25:21,686
Then let's begin next week.

436
00:25:22,754 --> 00:25:24,589
I'll handle pre-hospital triage first.

437
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:26,825
Only the critically ill and complex cases

438
00:25:27,125 --> 00:25:28,493
will take up your time.

439
00:25:28,727 --> 00:25:29,227
No problem.

440
00:25:29,594 --> 00:25:30,128
Thank you, Director.

441
00:25:32,797 --> 00:25:33,465
And another thing:

442
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:35,000
Huiyang has two

443
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:35,634
TAVR cases, right?

444
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:36,434
When are you planning to do them?

445
00:25:36,801 --> 00:25:37,435
Next Tuesday.

446
00:25:39,104 --> 00:25:39,838
No need to wait until Tuesday.

447
00:25:39,838 --> 00:25:40,772
I'm free this Sunday.

448
00:25:40,906 --> 00:25:41,473
Let's do them Sunday.

449
00:25:41,907 --> 00:25:42,440
Sunday?

450
00:25:43,408 --> 00:25:44,609
Are you sure you don't need more rest?

451
00:25:45,143 --> 00:25:45,710
I don't.

452
00:25:45,744 --> 00:25:46,745
I rested enough in Europe.

453
00:25:47,445 --> 00:25:48,446
Then thank you, Director.

454
00:25:49,014 --> 00:25:49,481
Thank you.

455
00:26:13,271 --> 00:26:14,306
You finished surgery?

456
00:26:15,907 --> 00:26:16,975
How did it go?

457
00:26:17,609 --> 00:26:18,643
Smoothly. Very smoothly.

458
00:26:19,210 --> 00:26:20,712
I heard you added another case.

459
00:26:21,546 --> 00:26:23,882
Yes. More work for the capable.

460
00:26:24,783 --> 00:26:26,384
Cardiology was getting anxious waiting.

461
00:26:31,289 --> 00:26:32,591
It's fine. Director Sheng said

462
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:33,692
he'll handle the operating room.

463
00:26:34,125 --> 00:26:35,393
He has also spoken with Zhou Xiaofeng.

464
00:26:36,361 --> 00:26:37,395
The hybrid operating room

465
00:26:37,395 --> 00:26:38,797
is shared by both departments.

466
00:26:39,030 --> 00:26:39,364
And

467
00:26:39,364 --> 00:26:39,764
TAVR

468
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:41,132
is a cross-disciplinary service anyway.

469
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:42,000
As long as you

470
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,335
coordinate in advance, it's fine.

471
00:26:51,910 --> 00:26:52,744
Since you got back,

472
00:26:52,744 --> 00:26:53,845
you've been working nonstop.

473
00:26:53,945 --> 00:26:55,246
Can your body handle it?

474
00:26:55,947 --> 00:26:56,615
No problem.

475
00:26:57,415 --> 00:26:58,450
I'm perfectly healthy.

476
00:26:58,683 --> 00:26:59,985
I sleep well and eat well.

477
00:27:01,252 --> 00:27:01,753
Look.

478
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,054
I'll take a bite to prove it.

479
00:27:11,162 --> 00:27:11,863
And look—

480
00:27:12,197 --> 00:27:13,064
every day you prepare

481
00:27:13,131 --> 00:27:14,432
red, green, yellow, and white foods for me.

482
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,034
Anyone would be healthy eating this.

483
00:27:22,440 --> 00:27:24,809
Patients for the specialty valve clinic,

484
00:27:25,276 --> 00:27:26,311
number 22,

485
00:27:26,678 --> 00:27:27,545
please proceed to Room 8.

486
00:27:27,545 --> 00:27:28,413
No problem, right?

487
00:27:28,513 --> 00:27:29,014
For consultation.

488
00:27:29,014 --> 00:27:29,681
Please wait a moment.

489
00:27:29,748 --> 00:27:30,315
Our Director Lin

490
00:27:30,348 --> 00:27:30,682
will take a careful look.

491
00:27:30,682 --> 00:27:31,483
Number 22.

492
00:27:31,683 --> 00:27:32,584
Doctor, doctor.

493
00:27:32,751 --> 00:27:33,652
Please look at mine.

494
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:34,653
Director Lin, take a look at me.

495
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:35,887
Don't rush.

496
00:27:35,887 --> 00:27:36,721
Everyone, please don't crowd.

497
00:27:36,721 --> 00:27:37,822
Don't crowd.

498
00:27:38,189 --> 00:27:38,923
There's no need to rush.

499
00:27:38,957 --> 00:27:39,824
We'll go in order.

500
00:27:39,924 --> 00:27:41,126
Your number will be called on the screen.

501
00:27:41,126 --> 00:27:41,793
Just watch for your number.

502
00:27:41,793 --> 00:27:43,128
Please don't all stand here.

503
00:27:43,294 --> 00:27:44,262
There are chairs outside.

504
00:27:44,596 --> 00:27:45,130
Please wait outside.

505
00:27:45,130 --> 00:27:46,164
One at a time.

506
00:27:46,264 --> 00:27:46,598
One at a time.

507
00:27:46,598 --> 00:27:47,665
You're the one after next.

508
00:27:47,766 --> 00:27:48,199
The one after next.

509
00:27:48,566 --> 00:27:49,434
You still have a while.

510
00:27:49,768 --> 00:27:50,769
Sir, please wait outside first.

511
00:27:50,769 --> 00:27:51,870
Wait outside. It's still early.

512
00:27:52,470 --> 00:27:53,238
Watch the numbers.

513
00:27:54,239 --> 00:27:55,040
Please wait a little longer.

514
00:27:55,907 --> 00:27:56,441
Seriously.

515
00:27:56,808 --> 00:27:57,809
No matter how skilled he is,

516
00:27:58,209 --> 00:27:59,310
even if he's a genius,

517
00:27:59,477 --> 00:28:00,812
he still has to consider others.

518
00:28:00,912 --> 00:28:01,746
What is this becoming?

519
00:28:02,213 --> 00:28:02,914
He's monopolizing the operating room.

520
00:28:04,582 --> 00:28:05,250
Director Zhou

521
00:28:05,250 --> 00:28:06,718
probably can't bear to criticize him right now.

522
00:28:07,152 --> 00:28:08,453
Director Lin just lost a family member,

523
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:09,854
and his last one at that.

524
00:28:10,455 --> 00:28:12,891
Yes, everyone understands grief.

525
00:28:13,091 --> 00:28:13,992
But I still think

526
00:28:13,992 --> 00:28:15,393
Director Zhou is too soft-hearted.

527
00:28:15,927 --> 00:28:17,562
He's protecting their brotherhood.

528
00:28:17,796 --> 00:28:18,930
But Lin Yi isn't showing him the same consideration.

529
00:28:21,866 --> 00:28:22,400
So how was it

530
00:28:22,634 --> 00:28:23,234
going to Europe?

531
00:28:23,668 --> 00:28:24,669
Anything interesting?

532
00:28:25,303 --> 00:28:26,604
What could be interesting?

533
00:28:27,238 --> 00:28:28,807
Just more meetings in a different place.

534
00:28:43,321 --> 00:28:43,721
Come in.

535
00:28:46,224 --> 00:28:46,825
Director Zhou.

536
00:28:48,693 --> 00:28:49,194
Zhang Zhen.

537
00:28:54,265 --> 00:28:54,833
Impossible.

538
00:28:55,967 --> 00:28:57,335
There must be some misunderstanding.

539
00:28:58,269 --> 00:28:59,070
The whistleblower provided

540
00:28:59,170 --> 00:28:59,971
conclusive evidence

541
00:29:00,071 --> 00:29:01,272
and a complete chain of proof.

542
00:29:01,606 --> 00:29:02,373
Zhang Zhen and the others

543
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:04,042
each accepted

544
00:29:04,042 --> 00:29:04,909
a 10,000-yuan cash gift from Aixinkang.

545
00:29:05,877 --> 00:29:07,078
The hospital's discipline committee

546
00:29:07,078 --> 00:29:08,613
is investigating everyone

547
00:29:08,646 --> 00:29:09,514
involved in the Europe trip.

548
00:29:10,081 --> 00:29:10,548
Director Zhou,

549
00:29:11,082 --> 00:29:12,150
as his supervisor,

550
00:29:12,317 --> 00:29:12,884
we also need you

551
00:29:12,884 --> 00:29:13,785
to cooperate with the investigation.

552
00:29:17,555 --> 00:29:18,156
I understand.

553
00:29:19,624 --> 00:29:20,992
But you said "Zhang Zhen and the others."

554
00:29:21,693 --> 00:29:22,127
Yes.

555
00:29:22,961 --> 00:29:23,962
Does that mean

556
00:29:23,962 --> 00:29:25,330
other people from our hospital

557
00:29:25,630 --> 00:29:26,831
are involved too?

558
00:29:27,232 --> 00:29:28,366
At present, only Zhang Zhen.

559
00:29:28,399 --> 00:29:29,434
The others involved

560
00:29:42,514 --> 00:29:43,214
are from other hospitals.

561
00:29:43,915 --> 00:29:44,582
Ten thousand?

562
00:29:45,683 --> 00:29:47,852
Yes.

563
00:29:48,486 --> 00:29:50,121
I heard the amount

564
00:29:51,156 --> 00:29:52,090
varied by the doctor's rank.

565
00:29:52,123 --> 00:29:53,625
Wasn't Dr. Zhang

566
00:29:55,527 --> 00:29:56,361
only promoted to attending two years ago?

567
00:29:57,529 --> 00:29:58,463
Ten thousand yuan.

568
00:30:00,865 --> 00:30:01,933
The damage is bad enough,

569
00:30:03,401 --> 00:30:05,003
but the insult is worse.

570
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:06,805
If everyone on the trip got one,

571
00:30:06,805 --> 00:30:07,806
then...

572
00:30:08,039 --> 00:30:09,507
Director Lin definitely wouldn't.

573
00:30:09,974 --> 00:30:11,176
Of course not. I know him.

574
00:30:11,176 --> 00:30:11,809
If he had ever reached out for money,

575
00:30:11,809 --> 00:30:12,710
with his skills,

576
00:30:13,144 --> 00:30:13,645
he'd have been rich long ago.

577
00:30:14,078 --> 00:30:15,313
Exactly.

578
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:17,515
We think so too.

579
00:30:17,549 --> 00:30:19,250
Then will Dr. Zhang

580
00:30:19,584 --> 00:30:20,318
be severely punished?

581
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:22,387
It's not that simple.

582
00:30:23,154 --> 00:30:24,122
If it were only internal discipline,

583
00:30:24,122 --> 00:30:24,756
that would already be

584
00:30:24,989 --> 00:30:26,157
the lightest outcome for him.

585
00:30:26,291 --> 00:30:27,725
He was reported by

586
00:30:27,959 --> 00:30:28,927
another medical-device distributor.

587
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:29,794
They have evidence.

588
00:30:30,094 --> 00:30:31,029
It's been proven,

589
00:30:31,863 --> 00:30:33,064
and exposed online too.

590
00:30:33,364 --> 00:30:33,865
As things stand,

591
00:30:33,932 --> 00:30:35,133
our hospital

592
00:30:35,466 --> 00:30:37,435
definitely won't keep him.

593
00:30:39,437 --> 00:30:40,071
Whether he can retain his medical license

594
00:30:41,806 --> 00:30:43,641
is uncertain.

595
00:30:44,309 --> 00:30:45,844
He's only in his early thirties.

596
00:30:46,311 --> 00:30:47,445
You study for over a decade,

597
00:30:48,313 --> 00:30:49,314
then residency training,

598
00:30:51,249 --> 00:30:52,350
then specialty training.

599
00:30:53,051 --> 00:30:54,586
How many night shifts did you work?

600
00:30:54,652 --> 00:30:56,788
How many emergencies did you handle?

601
00:30:57,488 --> 00:30:59,324
You made it all the way here, Zhang Zhen.

602
00:31:00,124 --> 00:31:01,693
Are you the only one who needs money?

603
00:31:01,826 --> 00:31:02,293
Fine. You need money.

604
00:31:02,994 --> 00:31:04,262
All right.

605
00:31:06,965 --> 00:31:08,266
Ten thousand yuan.

606
00:31:08,800 --> 00:31:10,235
Just ten thousand.

607
00:31:11,269 --> 00:31:13,204
And you traded more than a decade for it.

608
00:31:21,212 --> 00:31:21,846
That's the whole situation.

609
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:42,867
Come in.

610
00:31:48,973 --> 00:31:50,174
D-Director.

611
00:31:51,943 --> 00:31:52,877
Why?

612
00:31:54,045 --> 00:31:55,313
Were you really that desperate for money?

613
00:31:56,481 --> 00:31:57,548
A 10,000-yuan cash gift

614
00:31:59,250 --> 00:32:00,118
destroyed your future.

615
00:32:02,754 --> 00:32:03,288
Was it worth it?

616
00:32:04,956 --> 00:32:06,124
Director.

617
00:32:07,392 --> 00:32:08,559
I really had no choice.

618
00:32:09,160 --> 00:32:10,561
I just bought a home this year.

619
00:32:10,561 --> 00:32:11,596
My monthly mortgage

620
00:32:12,230 --> 00:32:13,464
is crushing.

621
00:32:13,865 --> 00:32:14,966
My wife's salary and mine together

622
00:32:15,333 --> 00:32:16,334
are barely

623
00:32:18,236 --> 00:32:19,370
enough to get by.

624
00:32:19,871 --> 00:32:21,806
And for the past two or three months,

625
00:32:23,408 --> 00:32:24,542
our performance bonuses have been so low.

626
00:32:24,709 --> 00:32:25,910
Starting last month,

627
00:32:26,711 --> 00:32:27,245
I couldn't keep up with the payments.

628
00:32:28,713 --> 00:32:29,714
Director.

629
00:32:29,747 --> 00:32:31,249
But before this,

630
00:32:31,416 --> 00:32:31,849
I truly never accepted

631
00:32:35,486 --> 00:32:36,854
any benefit from anyone.

632
00:32:37,889 --> 00:32:38,456
Really.

633
00:32:38,456 --> 00:32:40,024
So that ten thousand

634
00:32:40,291 --> 00:32:41,826
felt like a lifeline to me.

635
00:32:42,560 --> 00:32:44,128
If you were struggling, you should've told me.

636
00:32:46,998 --> 00:32:47,999
Why didn't you tell me?

637
00:32:48,032 --> 00:32:49,567
I didn't want to trouble you again.

638
00:33:00,111 --> 00:33:00,611
You already had enough on your plate.

639
00:33:03,014 --> 00:33:04,749
Director.

640
00:33:06,184 --> 00:33:06,951
From the first day I followed you,

641
00:33:06,951 --> 00:33:07,752
I always saw you

642
00:33:09,887 --> 00:33:11,489
as my role model.

643
00:33:12,690 --> 00:33:13,558
But over time, I realized

644
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:14,525
I was falling farther and farther behind.

645
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:17,895
I could never reach your level.

646
00:33:20,331 --> 00:33:21,666
I used to be excellent too.

647
00:33:22,867 --> 00:33:24,035
I was even on

648
00:33:24,068 --> 00:33:24,669
my high school's honor roll.

649
00:33:25,837 --> 00:33:27,472
But now, whenever I go home,

650
00:33:29,273 --> 00:33:30,041
and see my old

651
00:33:30,041 --> 00:33:31,009
high school classmates

652
00:33:31,075 --> 00:33:32,043
driving luxury cars

653
00:33:32,844 --> 00:33:33,945
and living in mansions,

654
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:37,482
I start doubting myself.

655
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:39,951
I earned a doctorate.

656
00:33:39,984 --> 00:33:41,386
I'm over thirty.

657
00:33:43,654 --> 00:33:45,189
I work hard every single day.

658
00:33:45,256 --> 00:33:45,690
And yet

659
00:33:46,090 --> 00:33:47,091
every month,

660
00:33:47,125 --> 00:33:48,793
I can't even make my mortgage payment.

661
00:33:49,894 --> 00:33:50,895
But I told myself it was okay.

662
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:53,231
I told myself,

663
00:33:54,799 --> 00:33:55,466
"Zhang Zhen,

664
00:33:56,768 --> 00:33:57,602
you can do this.

665
00:33:58,436 --> 00:33:59,504
As long as you keep working,

666
00:34:00,371 --> 00:34:01,472
your seniority will rise,

667
00:34:01,906 --> 00:34:03,040
and so will your pay."

668
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:06,277
And

669
00:34:07,245 --> 00:34:08,713
when I wore this white coat,

670
00:34:08,713 --> 00:34:09,747
I truly felt

671
00:34:10,548 --> 00:34:11,582
proud.

672
00:34:12,450 --> 00:34:13,551
During your two years in Guizhou,

673
00:34:14,252 --> 00:34:15,286
I fought my way

674
00:34:15,353 --> 00:34:16,154
through the department alone.

675
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:18,623
I gave it everything I had.

676
00:34:19,223 --> 00:34:19,924
I was waiting for the day

677
00:34:19,957 --> 00:34:20,825
you came back

678
00:34:21,959 --> 00:34:22,727
and saw that Zhang Zhen

679
00:34:23,428 --> 00:34:24,028
was different,

680
00:34:24,495 --> 00:34:24,996
that I'd grown.

681
00:34:26,030 --> 00:34:27,065
I wanted you to see

682
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,168
that when you chose me,

683
00:34:31,569 --> 00:34:32,503
you hadn't chosen the wrong person.

684
00:34:38,042 --> 00:34:39,277
But this time,

685
00:34:41,612 --> 00:34:43,081
I truly was wrong.

686
00:34:46,284 --> 00:34:48,786
I struggled all the way to today.

687
00:34:48,986 --> 00:34:52,223
I really did my best, Director.

688
00:34:54,559 --> 00:34:55,560
I'm sorry.

689
00:35:21,652 --> 00:35:22,119
President Wang,

690
00:35:22,553 --> 00:35:24,288
Zhang Zhen has always been diligent and responsible.

691
00:35:24,722 --> 00:35:25,556
His clinical ability

692
00:35:25,556 --> 00:35:27,191
is among the best of his peers.

693
00:35:28,092 --> 00:35:29,527
Of course, wrong is wrong.

694
00:35:30,595 --> 00:35:31,896
But since this was his first offense,

695
00:35:32,230 --> 00:35:32,630
could you give him

696
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:33,764
a chance to start over?

697
00:35:34,065 --> 00:35:35,199
I understand how you feel.

698
00:35:36,200 --> 00:35:37,001
We all know

699
00:35:38,169 --> 00:35:39,437
how difficult it is

700
00:35:39,904 --> 00:35:40,838
to train an attending physician.

701
00:35:41,439 --> 00:35:42,073
But this time,

702
00:35:42,507 --> 00:35:43,608
it's a matter of principle.

703
00:35:44,442 --> 00:35:45,877
Could you consider a fine,

704
00:35:46,010 --> 00:35:46,511
a demotion,

705
00:35:46,611 --> 00:35:47,745
or transfer him to a branch hospital?

706
00:35:48,279 --> 00:35:48,913
Direct dismissal

707
00:35:48,913 --> 00:35:50,114
seems too severe.

708
00:35:50,882 --> 00:35:52,049
At least let him keep some dignity

709
00:35:52,116 --> 00:35:53,251
and resign voluntarily.

710
00:35:55,753 --> 00:35:56,854
The pharmaceutical company

711
00:35:56,954 --> 00:35:57,788
filed a real-name report.

712
00:35:58,389 --> 00:35:59,590
If you were the president,

713
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:00,725
what would you do?

714
00:36:15,806 --> 00:36:17,208
He really made one foolish mistake.

715
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:20,077
I know his character.

716
00:36:21,245 --> 00:36:22,280
He's not that kind of person.

717
00:36:23,714 --> 00:36:24,949
Fortunately, it was only his first offense.

718
00:36:26,384 --> 00:36:27,485
If he'd been doing it repeatedly,

719
00:36:27,685 --> 00:36:28,719
you'd be accountable too.

720
00:36:30,054 --> 00:36:30,555
Yes.

721
00:36:31,222 --> 00:36:32,190
I'm sorry, President Wang.

722
00:36:32,957 --> 00:36:34,692
I failed to notice it. I bear responsibility.

723
00:36:35,426 --> 00:36:36,193
But if we handle it this way...

724
00:36:36,227 --> 00:36:37,328
There is no "but."

725
00:36:37,795 --> 00:36:38,796
Handling him this way now

726
00:36:39,630 --> 00:36:40,831
is meant to warn

727
00:36:40,865 --> 00:36:41,632
everyone else.

728
00:36:42,633 --> 00:36:43,467
They need to understand:

729
00:36:43,968 --> 00:36:44,702
don't reach out your hand.

730
00:36:45,169 --> 00:36:45,903
If you do, you'll be caught.

731
00:36:46,637 --> 00:36:47,305
And you

732
00:36:48,105 --> 00:36:49,073
need to learn from this.

733
00:36:49,607 --> 00:36:51,542
Strengthen integrity education in the department

734
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:53,044
and make sure

735
00:36:53,211 --> 00:36:53,844
nothing like this

736
00:37:11,896 --> 00:37:12,063
Director.

737
00:37:12,196 --> 00:37:12,730
Hello, Director.

738
00:37:50,568 --> 00:37:51,836
What are you measuring over there?

739
00:37:52,503 --> 00:37:53,638
I was thinking of making you

740
00:37:53,638 --> 00:37:54,572
a new sheath for that knife.

741
00:37:54,972 --> 00:37:56,574
The knife itself looks fine,

742
00:37:57,241 --> 00:37:58,442
but the leather cover

743
00:37:58,909 --> 00:38:00,044
is too flimsy.

744
00:38:00,678 --> 00:38:02,313
You rushed forward the moment he drew it.

745
00:38:02,880 --> 00:38:04,215
What if it really had been a weapon?

746
00:38:04,815 --> 00:38:05,983
That's exactly what I was afraid of.

747
00:38:07,852 --> 00:38:08,486
Two years ago,

748
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:09,520
after what happened with Zhuang Jiashun,

749
00:38:10,054 --> 00:38:11,088
I swore

750
00:38:12,289 --> 00:38:12,957
that as long as I'm here,

751
00:38:13,224 --> 00:38:13,991
I won't let anyone

752
00:38:14,091 --> 00:38:14,759
hurt you.

753
00:38:37,548 --> 00:38:39,317
So Zhang Zhen was fired just like that?

754
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:42,853
Didn't he return the money?

755
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:44,155
Was there really no room to maneuver?

756
00:38:44,388 --> 00:38:45,322
The notice is already out.

757
00:38:45,356 --> 00:38:46,324
What room is left?

758
00:38:47,491 --> 00:38:49,026
He was Zhou's top protégé.

759
00:38:49,193 --> 00:38:50,628
Didn't Zhou step in to protect him?

760
00:38:51,429 --> 00:38:52,763
He wouldn't even protect his own mother.

761
00:38:52,863 --> 00:38:53,331
Did you forget?

762
00:38:54,065 --> 00:38:55,800
He's lucky he kept himself clean.

763
00:38:56,200 --> 00:38:57,668
Poor Zhang Zhen.

764
00:38:57,868 --> 00:38:59,003
All for ten thousand yuan.

765
00:38:59,470 --> 00:38:59,904
What a bitter end.

766
00:39:01,172 --> 00:39:02,773
That old saying is true:

767
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:04,842
Temptation only works when someone leaves an opening.

768
00:39:05,109 --> 00:39:06,711
Young people don't earn enough.

769
00:39:06,811 --> 00:39:07,678
The moment temptation appears,

770
00:39:07,712 --> 00:39:08,646
they look for a shortcut.

771
00:39:08,746 --> 00:39:09,246
Exactly.

772
00:39:09,714 --> 00:39:10,815
In our profession,

773
00:39:11,215 --> 00:39:12,650
you still need some idealism.

774
00:39:13,484 --> 00:39:14,752
If all you want is big money,

775
00:39:14,785 --> 00:39:15,920
there are easier ways to make it.

776
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:17,888
Resisting temptation

777
00:39:18,189 --> 00:39:19,623
is a lesson in itself.

778
00:39:19,924 --> 00:39:21,325
Every generation is different.

779
00:39:21,358 --> 00:39:22,193
Dr. Zhan,

780
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,961
your generation benefited from the times.

781
00:39:24,195 --> 00:39:25,596
You were assigned a job after graduation,

782
00:39:25,596 --> 00:39:26,364
got welfare housing,

783
00:39:26,797 --> 00:39:27,932
and faced less competition.

784
00:39:27,965 --> 00:39:29,367
Can young doctors today

785
00:39:29,367 --> 00:39:30,167
really be compared with that?

786
00:39:30,367 --> 00:39:31,068
The moment they graduate, they enter the rat race.

787
00:39:31,168 --> 00:39:32,002
They compete themselves to exhaustion.

788
00:39:32,403 --> 00:39:33,904
And still have mortgages and car loans.

789
00:39:34,171 --> 00:39:35,606
Exactly. It's too hard.

790
00:39:35,606 --> 00:39:36,874
Every generation of young people

791
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:38,409
says the previous generation

792
00:39:38,476 --> 00:39:39,443
enjoyed the dividends of the era,

793
00:39:39,710 --> 00:39:41,645
and only theirs got the worst deal.

794
00:39:42,146 --> 00:39:44,648
I have elderly parents and young children too.

795
00:39:45,683 --> 00:39:46,050
Director Zhou.

796
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:46,784
Director. Director Zhou.

797
00:39:46,984 --> 00:39:47,351
Director.

798
00:39:56,927 --> 00:39:57,762
I'm very sorry

799
00:40:00,998 --> 00:40:01,866
about what happened to Zhang Zhen.

800
00:40:05,770 --> 00:40:06,837
But there's no use dwelling on it.

801
00:40:10,274 --> 00:40:11,909
Today I want to ask everyone again:

802
00:40:14,311 --> 00:40:15,079
for the past few months,

803
00:40:15,513 --> 00:40:17,314
our department's performance has remained poor.

804
00:40:19,984 --> 00:40:21,385
Where do you think the problem lies?

805
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:24,488
And how should we solve it?

806
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:30,327
Director Zhan.

807
00:40:31,762 --> 00:40:32,663
You're the most senior here.

808
00:40:33,397 --> 00:40:34,165
You tell us.

809
00:40:37,535 --> 00:40:38,936
As for performance,

810
00:40:40,070 --> 00:40:41,672
we can't become fat in one bite.

811
00:40:42,373 --> 00:40:43,507
We need to take the long view.

812
00:40:45,543 --> 00:40:46,544
Director Zhan,

813
00:40:47,044 --> 00:40:48,078
Cardiac Surgery

814
00:40:48,078 --> 00:40:49,480
is already coming at us aggressively.

815
00:40:50,014 --> 00:40:51,882
We don't have the luxury of taking our time.

816
00:40:52,483 --> 00:40:53,551
The pie is only this big.

817
00:40:53,918 --> 00:40:55,853
The Heart Center

818
00:40:55,886 --> 00:40:56,687
can only absorb so many patients.

819
00:40:56,854 --> 00:40:57,922
If Cardiac Surgery gets more,

820
00:40:58,055 --> 00:40:58,856
we get fewer.

821
00:40:59,523 --> 00:41:00,691
Cardiac Surgery has opened

822
00:41:00,724 --> 00:41:01,759
many new specialty clinics.

823
00:41:01,992 --> 00:41:03,160
They now do their own echocardiograms,

824
00:41:03,194 --> 00:41:03,761
angiography,

825
00:41:03,894 --> 00:41:04,628
and everything else,

826
00:41:04,728 --> 00:41:05,796
weakening our upstream advantage.

827
00:41:05,930 --> 00:41:06,463
Exactly.

828
00:41:06,831 --> 00:41:08,199
Especially in valve disease.

829
00:41:08,532 --> 00:41:09,800
Such a large piece of the pie

830
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:11,469
is about to be taken right out of our hands.

831
00:41:13,037 --> 00:41:13,871
That's what I'm saying.

832
00:41:14,505 --> 00:41:15,039
Intervention

833
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:16,974
was originally our strength.

834
00:41:17,074 --> 00:41:17,575
Right?

835
00:41:17,842 --> 00:41:19,243
Now Cardiac Surgery openly wants to take it.

836
00:41:19,510 --> 00:41:20,878
That puts us

837
00:41:21,078 --> 00:41:21,745
in a very passive position.

838
00:41:21,846 --> 00:41:23,247
Don't you agree?

839
00:41:23,414 --> 00:41:24,481
Over the past two months,

840
00:41:24,515 --> 00:41:25,983
the loss of patients has been severe.

841
00:41:26,116 --> 00:41:27,318
Some patients

842
00:41:27,351 --> 00:41:28,719
had already signed admission forms with us

843
00:41:28,719 --> 00:41:29,520
and were admitted,

844
00:41:30,287 --> 00:41:30,988
then transferred out.

845
00:41:31,121 --> 00:41:31,689
Meanwhile,

846
00:41:32,022 --> 00:41:32,890
many elderly chronic-care patients

847
00:41:32,923 --> 00:41:33,924
stay for more than ten days,

848
00:41:34,158 --> 00:41:35,192
tying up beds completely.

849
00:41:35,526 --> 00:41:36,627
Only ten days?

850
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:37,828
I have one who's been here over a month.

851
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:38,963
Over a month?

852
00:41:39,196 --> 00:41:40,030
That's ridiculous.

853
00:41:40,364 --> 00:41:41,198
I can't even afford my rent now.

854
00:41:41,565 --> 00:41:43,133
With things like this,

855
00:41:47,671 --> 00:41:48,272
we don't know

856
00:41:48,372 --> 00:41:49,006
when it'll end.

857
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:50,174
Complaining won't solve anything.

858
00:41:50,407 --> 00:41:51,842
We can't control

859
00:41:52,810 --> 00:41:53,744
competition between departments.

860
00:41:53,811 --> 00:41:55,212
Nor can we expect the other side

861
00:41:55,813 --> 00:41:56,914
to follow the old rules.

862
00:41:56,947 --> 00:41:58,249
We can only rely on ourselves.

863
00:41:58,582 --> 00:41:59,750
What they take from us,

864
00:42:01,285 --> 00:42:02,286
we'll take back.

865
00:42:03,153 --> 00:42:04,455
Starting today,

866
00:42:08,425 --> 00:42:09,159
from the moment a patient

867
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,095
is admitted,

868
00:42:11,128 --> 00:42:12,029
we must improve their experience

869
00:42:12,563 --> 00:42:13,964
and earn their trust.

870
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:15,366
Tests and examinations must be expedited.

871
00:42:16,066 --> 00:42:17,534
Surgical preparation must be shortened.

872
00:42:18,202 --> 00:42:19,570
If something can be scheduled for the next day,

873
00:42:20,204 --> 00:42:21,272
don't delay it until the third.

874
00:42:21,305 --> 00:42:22,673
To improve bed turnover,

875
00:42:23,707 --> 00:42:25,209
we must first increase

876
00:42:25,776 --> 00:42:27,478
higher-value cases

877
00:42:27,711 --> 00:42:29,280
Only then can we avoid long-term bed occupancy.

878
00:42:30,748 --> 00:42:31,348
I know

879
00:42:32,182 --> 00:42:33,250
I still haven't earned

880
00:42:33,684 --> 00:42:34,885
everyone's full trust.

881
00:42:35,352 --> 00:42:36,520
